    {
      "id": 28999,
      "post_number": 14,
      "username": "Z0NK0UT",
      "name": "Chad @ LZX Industries",
      "created_at": "2022-10-02T16:59:01.691Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-02T16:59:01.691Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Welcome. Your flower power video looks great!<br>\nThis thread is for discussing \u201cDJing with live visuals\u201d, so you might consider sharing in the gallery thread:</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"686\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://yyz1.discourse-cdn.com/flex031/user_avatar/community.lzxindustries.net/wednesdayayay/48/70_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.lzxindustries.net/t/community-video-gallery/686\">Community video gallery</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/forum/gallery/33\"><span data-category-id=\"33\" data-parent-category-id=\"13\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Gallery</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I don\u2019t know that we have one place for us to post our videos to that we want to share with the community. I may have just missed the thread. \nanyway \nI\u2019ll start with some vidiot feedback \n\nthis was using two cameras two projectors and one vidiot \nwhat have you all been working on?\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 13,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29317,
      "post_number": 15,
      "username": "brendanleespengler",
      "name": "Brendan",
      "created_at": "2022-10-25T23:04:09.040Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-25T23:04:09.040Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I need a solid recommendation for a converter for ESG3 to HDMI projector for an upcoming live gig,  (Component/YPbPr to HDMI). Performing at the Music Box in Nola, if anyone\u2019s been. I saw photos of the projections for the Meridian Bros. a couple weeks ago and the place looks amazing.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": null,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29320,
      "post_number": 16,
      "username": "Dr_Rek",
      "name": "Derek Sajbel",
      "created_at": "2022-10-25T23:37:23.454Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-25T23:39:36.951Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hey! Probably better threads for that discussion, but best thing I\u2019ve found so far (if you are fine with 30 fps, which is fine for almost all live performance situations) is this one: <a href=\"https://smartavi.com/cvh-01-v2/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CVH-01 V2 - SmartAVI</a></p>\n<p>A converter that supports 60 fps and 10-bit color, I\u2019m still on the hunt</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 15,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29321,
      "post_number": 17,
      "username": "brendanleespengler",
      "name": "Brendan",
      "created_at": "2022-10-25T23:46:34.715Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-25T23:46:34.715Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I need a component to HDMI converter, from ESG to projector.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 16,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29322,
      "post_number": 18,
      "username": "Dr_Rek",
      "name": "Derek Sajbel",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T00:08:46.368Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T00:08:46.368Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yes you will find most component inputs on converters and video mixers need the vga to rca component cable. This box should work with one of those.  They come in 3ft and 6ft <a href=\"https://www.monoprice.com/product?p_id=2170\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Monoprice 6ft VGA to 3 RCA Component Video Cable (HD15 - 3-RCA) - Monoprice.com</a></p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 17,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29323,
      "post_number": 19,
      "username": "brendanleespengler",
      "name": "Brendan",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T00:26:46.411Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T00:26:46.411Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Confusing. So is a cheap RCA to HDMI converter not a good option? Does the ESG3 have problems w the YPbPr outs v. the composite out? Do most venues have projector setups w HDMI inputs only? The handful I\u2019ve encountered recently do. What is the solution for VJing w ESG3?</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 18,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29328,
      "post_number": 21,
      "username": "Dr_Rek",
      "name": "Derek Sajbel",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T05:28:03.802Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T15:55:15.564Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Or there are lots of cheap Chinese options like this on Amazon</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox amazon\" data-onebox-src=\"https://www.amazon.com/Portta-N3CVRHP-Component-Converter-support/dp/B003VJ9RP6\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Portta-N3CVRHP-Component-Converter-support/dp/B003VJ9RP6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">amazon.com</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    \n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Portta-N3CVRHP-Component-Converter-support/dp/B003VJ9RP6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Amazon.com: Portta Component to HDMI Converter, Portta YPbPr Component RGB + R/L...</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Amazon.com: Portta Component to HDMI Converter, Portta YPbPr Component RGB + R/L Audio to HDMI Converter v1.3 Support 1080P 24bit 2 Channel Audio LPCM for HDTV PS3 PS4 HDVD Player Wii Xbox and More (Component to HDMI) : Electronics</p>\n\n<p>\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  <strong></strong>\n</p>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Color is 8-bit, and I\u2019ve no idea about quality, but probably worth checking out one model or another with free Amazon returns.</p>\n<p>I can\u2019t confirm it will work with esg3 but could. Anyone tried these type?</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 20,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29329,
      "post_number": 22,
      "username": "Marizu",
      "name": "Marizu Okereke",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T08:55:09.176Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T08:55:09.176Z",
      "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"brendanleespengler\" data-post=\"19\" data-topic=\"2282\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://yyz1.discourse-cdn.com/flex031/user_avatar/community.lzxindustries.net/brendanleespengler/48/317_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> brendanleespengler:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>So is a cheap RCA to HDMI converter not a good option? Does the ESG3 have problems w the YPbPr outs v. the composite out? Do most venues have projector setups w HDMI inputs only? The handful I\u2019ve encountered recently do. What is the solution for VJing w ESG3?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That\u2019s the HDMI to Component converter (if you use this for input, you probably want to use the version that has a built in scaler). They also make a Component to HDMI converter.</p>\n<p>I use both. From what I have seen, the Portta HDMI to Component converter (with scaler) is a bit soft. The Portta Component to HDMI looks good, but I\u2019m only working in PAL.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 21,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29331,
      "post_number": 23,
      "username": "Vdot",
      "name": "",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T15:26:02.467Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T15:26:02.467Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m planning on getting a Retrotink 5X soon for live projections. It\u2019s core purpose is for retro gaming with old SD game consoles on modern TVs which prioritizes low latency and has upscaling capabilities. I know some people on the Discord were discussing there\u2019s recently.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 15,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 29332,
      "post_number": 24,
      "username": "Dr_Rek",
      "name": "Derek Sajbel",
      "created_at": "2022-10-26T15:56:48.766Z",
      "updated_at": "2022-10-26T15:58:34.182Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I have a retrotink 2x and it works great for SD to HDMI stuff. FYI The 5x doesn\u2019t support 1080p source resolutions, and is pricey, so I decided against it.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 23,
      "is_wiki": false
